    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Outfielder Darryl Hamilton continues to struggle with a toe injury. A cortisone injection last Sunday did not help, and Hamilton did not know when he might return to a rehabilitation assignment.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Outfielder Darryl Hamilton continues to struggle with a toe injury. A cortisone injection last Sunday did not help, and Hamilton did not know when he might return to a rehabilitation assignment.</p>
        <p>''The days are mounting, the weeks are mounting and you still feel there's no progress,'' he said.</p>
        <p>The doctor who performed Hamilton's most recent toe surgery suggested that he have more drastic surgery after the season, but Hamilton said he was not considering that now.</p>
        <p>''I'm not going to give up on it,'' he said.</p>
        <p>The starter Rick Reed, who is on the disabled list with a broken bone in his left wrist, threw off a mound yesterday and team trainers were pleased with his progress, a possible indication he could return shortly after the All-Star Game break.</p>
        <p>TYLER KEPNER</p>
        <p>BASEBALL: NOTEBOOK</p>
